I love chihuahuas and thought I had to have this because Chihuahua, The Movie was so pleasant.  This one was horrible.  Not much good to say about it. Sorry.  I think I paid more for the postage than I did for the movie, too.  That ought to tell you something.
have enjoyed these movies with grandkids and hope to enjoy this one also they have seen all the others and we all enjoyed them i'm sure we won't be disappointed in this one either
It was really a kids movie.  I was hoping for a more life like/ adult type of movie.  I will set it on the shelf and wait for the grandkids to come watch it.

Fairly entertaining Chihuahua tale (bad pun intended) that has nothing to do with other movie. Still, a couple of kids with a ghost dog friend to help bring the family closer has got to at least keep you awake.

Wonderfully entertaining Family Feature about my favorite breed. Except this time a celebrity ghost who can only be seen by the Family pet. Leading to hilarious situations.
Lots of truly engaging performances from all the actors. A must see for all the family !

This movie is packed with fun moments for the whole family. Whether you are a dog lover or not, you will fall in love with every character in this movie. Morgan Most did an incredible job Directing this, as well as co-Writing it with Elyssa Davalos. The Most fun I've had in a long time!
Live this movie... all of the Chihuahua movies are so fun to watch. Hope they make more
Very cute my family to include our Chihuahua fur baby loved it and watch it at last three times a day.
good clean and on time. Just as i expected
Ok movie good for kids, my kids love it
Also boring and makes no sense. Poor acting, not worth the $

It was okay-but not nearly as good as the 'Beverly Hills Chihuahua' movies!
The best thing about the movie was actually the box showing the adorable chi in "flapper"style!
Was very pleased wlith this movie.  I am glad that I got it .
